programmes.show_description: Entertainment: Examine the influence that popular culture and entertainment have on daily life. As we gravitate to larger-than-life stories, outlandish myths begin to spread. (S1, ep 2)
In 1968, airmen in North Dakota spot a huge UFO over one of the US' most high security Air Force bases. Papua New Guinea village locals report strange objects in the sky in 1959. (S2, ep 5)
In 2000, two brothers spot a UFO the size of six football fields after a hunting in Idaho. A Madagascan city is plunged into darkness when a metal craft hovers overhead in 1954. (S2, ep 6)
Giorgio Tsoukalos takes a look back at the most extraordinary encounters that, as far as he's concerned, provide evidence of an extraterrestrial presence on Earth.
Hidden Flaws: When a DC-10 aeroplane explodes mid-flight over Iowa, the quick-thinking pilot saves 184 passengers. But what caused such a huge disaster? (5 of 6)
Man vs Machine: When a Boeing 777 crashes into San Francisco Airport with no warning, engineers race to figure out what could have caused such a disaster. (6 of 6)
Les' Spending Spree: Les can't stop buying, even though the store room is piled sky-high. In danger of being dubbed a hoarder, he faces big pressure to make some sales. (S7, ep 8)
Join antiques expert and presenter David Dickinson as more collectors try to sell their items to dealers. Will they strike a deal or take a chance at auction instead? (S9, ep 16)

Scott and Sheldon visit Regina, Avonlea and Moose Jaw as a mysterious treasure map leads them through Saskatchewan. (S3, ep 7)
Henry Cole and his fellow Junketeers go all rural when they buy a tractor at an agricultural auction. (S2, ep 3)
King of Orange Chicken: Rene declares himself the king of Orange, but Dusty isn't quite ready to concede the title. Meanwhile, Kenny accidentally reinvents the wheel. (S14, ep 7)
Lego My Locker: Darrell must deal with Kimber's eyes on a competitor, Dusty unpacks what could be the ultimate assistant and Rene pulls off one of his greatest profits. (S14, ep 8)
Seth's Big Bet: Ashley challenges Seth to a unique competition in the pawn shop. Should he lose, the world will hear the one thing he's been fighting to keep a secret. (S7, ep 11)
Oh No He Didn't: Les loses his temper when the kids suggest he sells their failing second store. With the family's livelihood at stake, Seth puts a sneaky plan into action. (S7, ep 12)
Rick's Big Triumph: A chandelier made out of KFC buckets lights up the shop and Rick gets amped up over a very special motorcycle.
Raging Bulls: Desperate to cull the exploding gator population, the swampers employ new, risky tactics to target giant breeding bulls. Joey and Zak create a feeding frenzy. (S11, ep 1)
Venom Warriors: Troy, Chase and Bill go deep diving in search of pythons but may have bitten off more than they can chew. Bruce and Zak venture into Viper Jungle. (S2, ep 2)
